  You dropped the events array (and the customHeaders for the shared secret) when you simplified the body — WAHA requires
  events to be a non-empty array from its enum list. Restore both:

  curl -X PUT http://localhost:3000/api/sessions/default \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "X-Api-Key: dc9cbf430e624d70a5ddf3e57b5ada76" \
    -d '{
      "config": {
        "webhooks": [{
          "url": "http://localhost:8080/api/webhooks/waha",
          "events": ["message"],
          "customHeaders": [{ "name": "X-Webhook-Secret", "value": "dev-webhook-secret-change-me" }]
        }]
      }
    }'

  Without customHeaders, WAHA's webhook calls to our backend won't carry X-Webhook-Secret, and our /api/webhooks/waha
  endpoint will reject them with 401 (per middleware.WebhookSecret in backend/internal/router/router.go) — so both fields
  matter here, not just events.